  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "If investment bankers are so rich then why doesn't everybody become one?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why not everyone becomes an investment banker, despite the potential for high financial rewards:\n\n1. **Educational Requirements**: Investment banking typically requires a strong educational background, often including a degree from a prestigious university and possibly an MBA or other advanced degrees. This can be a significant barrier for many.\n\n2. **Competitive Job Market**: The field of investment banking is highly competitive, with many candidates vying for a limited number of positions. Even well-qualified individuals may struggle to secure a job in this field.\n\n3. **Long Hours and Stress**: Investment banking is known for its demanding work culture, with long hours and high levels of stress. Many people may not be willing to sacrifice work-life balance and personal time for the sake of a high salary.\n\n4. **Skill Set**: Investment banking requires a specific skill set, including strong analytical abilities, numerical proficiency, and excellent communication skills. Not everyone has or wants to develop these skills.\n\n5. **Networking**: Success in investment banking often depends on personal connections and networking within the industry. Building a professional network can take time and effort that some may not be willing or able to invest.\n\n6. **Job Satisfaction**: Many people prioritize job satisfaction and passion over potential earnings. Investment banking may not be appealing to individuals who prefer careers in other fields that align more closely with their interests and values.\n\n7. **Burnout Potential**: The intense nature of the job can lead to burnout, causing many to leave the industry after a few years, even if they do start their careers in investment banking.\n\n8. **Career Alternates**: There are many lucrative and fulfilling career paths outside of investment banking, and not everyone is drawn to finance. Fields like technology, healthcare, or entrepreneurship can also offer high earning potential and job satisfaction.\n\nIn summary, while investment banking can be financially rewarding, various factors make it an impractical or undesirable career choice for many individuals.",
